headline: CORRECTION: Export Sales to China, Japan, and Unknown Destinations
article_text:
A correction was issued for this announcement on January 22, 2026. The initial version included reference to a sale of 500,302 metric tons of corn for delivery to unknown destinations. The corrected information is as follows:
---
Private exporters reported the following sales activities:
• 204,000 metric tons of soybeans for delivery to China during the 2025/2026 marketing year
• 110,000 metric tons of soybeans for delivery to unknown destinations during the 2025/2026 marketing year
• 435,000 metric tons of soybeans received in the reporting period for delivery to unknown destinations. Of the total, 360,000 metric tons is for delivery during the 2025/2026 marketing year, and 75,000 metric tons is for delivery during the 2026/2027 marketing year
• 260,000 metric tons of corn received in the reporting period for delivery to Japan during the 2025/2026 marketing year
• 320,302 metric tons of cornreceived in the reporting period for delivery to unknown destinations during the 2025/2026 marketing year
204,000 metric tons of soybeans for delivery to China during the 2025/2026 marketing year
110,000 metric tons of soybeans for delivery to unknown destinations during the 2025/2026 marketing year
435,000 metric tons of soybeans received in the reporting period for delivery to unknown destinations. Of the total, 360,000 metric tons is for delivery during the 2025/2026 marketing year, and 75,000 metric tons is for delivery during the 2026/2027 marketing year
260,000 metric tons of corn received in the reporting period for delivery to Japan during the 2025/2026 marketing year
320,302 metric tons of cornreceived in the reporting period for delivery to unknown destinations during the 2025/2026 marketing year
regions: China; East Asia and the Pacific; Japan
commodities: Grains, Feeds and Fodders; Corn; Oilseeds; Soybeans
